I fixed the problem with this query. I believe that the field may have been renamed since a few commits ago, so potentially no problems with upgrade.
{code}
[root@clcfrontend ~]# psql -h /var/lib/eucalyptus/db/data/ -p 8777 eucalyptus_config
psql (9.1.6)
Type "help" for help.

eucalyptus_config=# update config_static_property set config_static_prop_name='experimental.dns.enabled' where config_static_field_name='com.eucalyptus.util.dns.DnsResolvers.enabled';
{code}

Think I may have found the issue.  The way that result record sets are accessible is not idempotent by default:
{code}
/**
 * Returns an Iterator listing all (data) records.  This cycles through
 * the records, so each Iterator will start with a different record.
 */
public synchronized Iterator rrs()
{code}

Working on resolving.

Still seeing this message streaming twice per second in the logs after an upgrade:
{code}
2013-05-29 12:01:43  WARN | Failed to get property: experimental.dns.resolvers.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.dns.resolvers.RecursiveDnsResolver.enabled value=null propName=experimental.dns.resolvers.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
{code}
